Mike Teunissen claimed the first yellow jersey of this year’s Tour de France with a sprint victory in Saturday’s opening stage, which was also marked by Jakob Fuglsang’s crash. Teunissen pipped the former world champion Peter Sagan and Caleb Ewan to the finish line in Brussels. Fuglsang, who is among the favourites this year, hit the tarmac about 20km from the finish. The Astana team leader got back on his bike with blood on his face and right knee. He managed to reach the finish without losing time. The race started from the Belgian capital to honour the 50th anniversary of the first Tour victory of Eddy Merckx. Jeremy Whittle’s full race report to follow …